stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: Newly Identified Masquerade Domains
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description:
On January 10, 2018, a trusted third party reported numerous masquerading domains that are possibly associated with suspected threat actors. These domains are provided for early warning purposes to NCCIC stakeholders.
This technique is referred to as "domain masquerading", "typosquatting", or "URL hijacking", which is a form of cybersquatting (sitting on sites under someone else's brand or copyright). The intention is to target internet users who incorrectly type a website address into their web browser or who click on malicious links in phishing emails.
This activity was observed in the Government Facilities sector.

Recipients may share TLP:GREEN information with peers and partner organizations within their sector or community, but not via publicly accessible channels. Information in this category can be circulated widely within a particular community. TLP:GREEN information may not be released outside of the community.
